### Login an existing user with the JWT-based AuthenticationController (api-version-neutral).
### The handler validates the userId + password and returns a Bearer token to use on
### every subsequent /hosts, /hosts/{...}/menus, /hosts/{...}/dinners, /reservations,
### and /menu-reviews call.

POST {{host}}/authentication/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "userId": "xavierjohn2023",
    "password": "Amiko1232!"
}

### Expected response shape:
### HTTP/1.1 200 OK
### Content-Type: application/json
### {
###   "userId": "xavierjohn2023",
###   "firstName": "Xavier",
###   "lastName": "John",
###   "email": "someone@somewhere.com",
###   "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..."
### }
###
### Failure modes:
###   - Wrong password / unknown user -> 401 Unauthorized with
###     code: "Authentication.InvalidCredentials" (see Login-InvalidCredentials.http).
###
### Copy the `token` into `@token = ...` at the top of the other .http files (they
### send it as `Authorization: Bearer {{token}}`).